chairman of the department of business administration, and held several other 
titles. He was honored by UCLA alumni in 1968 and was chairman of the National 
Committee on Emeriti from 1965 to 1980. Earlier he had been a consultant to the 
European Productivity Agency in Paris and the Ford Foundation of India. In 
Westwood on Oct. 9. 
