<P>
HERBERT V. MUCHNIC; ORTHODONTIST, SCIENTIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Herbert V. Muchnic, 88, an orthodontist and research scientist who held state 
and national leadership positions in his field. Muchnic was educated at 
Northwestern University and USC Dental School.He maintained a practice in 
Beverly Hills, became mentor to many USC students and was president of the 
Pacific Coast Society of Orthodontists (1962-64) and the American Assn. of 
Orthodontists (1975). Working with Los Angeles plastic surgeon Bernard G. 
Sarnat, Muchnic conducted research on facial growth, observing changes that 
occur when growth centers of the jaw are removed. In a study published in 1971 
by the Journal of Anatomy (a British scientific journal) and the American 
Journal of Orthodontics, the two men reported on unsuspected parallels in 
facial growth patterns of children and adults. On Oct. 10 of cancer at his Los 
Angeles home. 
