<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: NEWBURY PARK; JUDGE RENEGES ON PROBATION PROMISE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DWAYNE BRAY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A porn actress from Newbury Park has shown no remorse for having sex with a 
14-year-old boy, a Ventura County judge said Monday, as he reneged on his 
promise to keep the woman from going to prison. 
</P>
<P>
 Laurie Arden, 45, pleaded guilty last month to four criminal counts in 
connection with the case, after Superior Court Judge Charles W. Campbell Jr. 
promised she would get probation for her crimes. 
</P>
<P>
 On Monday, Campbell told Arden he could not stick to his part of the agreement 
and allowed her until Thursday to withdraw her guilty plea -- or face a state 
prison sentence. 
</P>
<P>
 Campbell said he changed his mind after reading statements Arden made in a 
probation report. The judge said he was particularly distressed over one 
statement in which Arden said she seduced the boy because she had pity for him. 
</P>
<P>
 "When I read that, I thought to myself that I had made a significant mistake 
in saying that this person ought to be placed on probation," Campbell said. "I 
can't understand how somebody could say that." 
</P>
<P>
 Arden also said in the report that the boy initiated their sexual affair.  
</P>
<P>
 She pleaded guilty to two counts of unlawful sexual intercourse with a minor, 
one count of sexual penetration with a foreign object and one count of showing 
explicit photos to a minor. 
</P>
<P>
 Arden could face as many as six years in prison. DWAYNE BRAY 
</P>
</TEXT>
