<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Angel reliever Ken Patterson and catcher Andy Allanson, each of whom has his 
season derailed by bizarre circumstances, cleared waivers and elected to become 
free agents. 
</P>
<P>
 The Angels filled the two roster spots with pitcher Mike James and utility 
player Luis Raven.They also took pitcher Kyle Sebach off the roster and sent 
him outright to triple-A Vancouver. 
</P>
<P>
 Patterson, whom the Angels reacquired on their final day of spring training, 
was recalled to the big leagues April 24. He threw six pitches against the 
Boston Red Sox before tearing a ligament in his elbow, requiring season-ending 
surgery. 
</P>
<P>
 Allanson's contract was bought June 28 by the Angels, who then discovered that 
he had a broken right finger that necessitated surgery. He never played a game 
for the big league team. 
</P>
</TEXT>
