<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN ARRESTED IN FATAL PACOIMA SHOOTING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 22-year-old accused of fatally shooting a Pacoima man last month has been 
arrested in Fresno for the allegedly gang-related crime, Los Angeles police 
said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 Aaron Phillips of Fresno was arrested Friday after he went to a scheduled 
meeting with his parole officer in the San Joaquin Valley city, said LAPD 
Detective Frank Bishop. 
</P>
<P>
 Phillips is being held on suspicion of murder in the Sept. 26 slaying of Eric 
Blair, 27, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Blair and a group of men were talking outside a house at 12150 Garber St. in 
Pacoima when a gunman shot at them, striking Blair, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Witnesses later identified Phillips as the gunman, police said. Phillips 
disappeared after the shooting, but police now believe that was when he moved 
from Lake View Terrace to Fresno, Bishop said. 
</P>
<P>
 Investigators said Phillips is a member of the Bloods street gang and that the 
men Blair was with during the shooting were also Bloods. There is no evidence 
that Blair was a gang member, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Philips was being held Monday in Fresno County Jail without bail. 
</P>
