<HEADLINE>
<P>
MEETINGS WILL ADDRESS QUAKE DAMAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Community Redevelopment Agency will hold two meetings to discuss a plan to 
repair earthquake damage in Sherman Oaks and Studio City. 
</P>
<P>
 The Los Angeles City Council asked CRA officials to assist residents in 
rebuilding homes and businesses damaged by the Jan. 17 earthquake. 
</P>
<P>
 CRA officials, working with the 5th Council District and community 
representatives, devised an earthquake disaster assistance plan that would 
allow the communities to redevelop earthquake damaged areas in a five-year 
program. 
</P>
<P>
 The first meeting will be held Wednesday from 6 to 9 p.m. at Millikan Junior 
High School in Sherman Oaks. The next meeting is on Oct. 26 at the same time 
and place. 
</P>
<P>
 CRA commissioners will also hold a joint public hearing on the proposed plan 
Nov. 15 at 10 a.m. in the council chambers at City Hall. 
</P>
</TEXT>
