<TEXT>
<P>
 IBM to Consolidate PC Lines: Moving to reduce consumers' confusion about its 
products and regain lost market share, the company said it will reduce the 
number of product lines to four from nine. But Richard Thoman, the senior vice 
president who heads the PC Co. division, said International Business Machines 
Corp. will not see the benefits of its new strategy and its recent 
restructuring announced in July until mid-1995. The new brand names are IBM PC, 
for business computers; IBM PC Server, for machines connected on local area 
networks; ThinkPad, for portable computers, and Aptiva, for its personal 
computers targeted at home and family users. 
