<P>
 Roche Holding Will Cut 5,000 Jobs: The big Swiss-owned drug and chemical 
company said it will make the cuts over the next several months as it absorbs 
operations of U.S. drug maker Syntex Corp. Roche, inventor of the well-known 
tranquilizers Librium and Valium, completed its $5.3-billion buyout of Syntex, 
a pioneer in birth control pills, Aug. 31. The job cuts, amounting to about 8% 
