<HEADLINE>
<P>
EXECUTIVE SUITE: COMPANY TOWN; WARNER UNIT APPOINTS NEW VICE PRESIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Warner Music announced a long-awaited restructuring of some of its West Coast 
operations. 
</P>
<P>
 Paul Cooper, who had been senior vice president and West Coast general manager 
for Warner's Atlantic Records unit, was been named vice president of Los 
Angeles-based Warner Music-U.S. 
</P>
<P>
 Warner would not say who will replace Cooper, but sources said the company is 
expected to announce soon that it has replaced him with Ron Shapiro, Atlantic 
vice president for media and artists relations. The move would be unusual for 
Shapiro in that it is somewhat rare for publicists to get such senior 
management posts. 
</P>
<P>
 In his new job, Cooper will be responsible for developing a West Coast base 
for Warner Music-U.S. The move is part of a restructuring of Time Warner Inc.'s 
music operations that is being handled by Doug Morris, who was recently 
promoted from head of Warner's Atlantic Group to president and chief operating 
officer of Warner Music-U.S. 
</P>
<P>
 * Joel Hoffner was promoted to vice president of sales for MCA's Uni 
Distribution Corp. 
</P>
<P>
 * Virgin Records America named Peter Holden director of international. 
</P>
<P>
 * Michael Goodnight was named senior vice president and assistant controller 
for Warner Bros. 
</P>
<P>
 * The American Film Marketing Assn. promoted William A. Anderson to vice 
president of research and publications. 
</P>
<P>
 * Gary Berberet was named vice president of advertising and promotion at 
Genesis Entertainment. 
</P>
<P>
 * Nickelodeon Movies has named Jerry Beck vice president of animation. 
</P>
<P>
 * New Line Cinema and producer Steve Tisch signed child star Curtis Williams 
Jr. to a two-year development deal. 
</P>
<P>
 * Kathleen A. Duke was named senior vice president of business and legal 
affairs for International Film Guarantors. 
</P>
<P>
 * Gini Barrett, senior vice president at the Alliance of Motion Picture and 
Television Producers, was named to the advisory council of Progress LA to 
promote economic development in Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
 * Yair Landau was promoted to senior vice president of finance and corporate 
development for Sony Pictures Entertainment. 
</P>
<P>
 * United Paramount Network named former 20th Television executive Leonard J. 
Grossi as a senior executive vice president. 
</P>
<P>
 * Agent Robert Kass has left Silver/Kass & Massetti to join Innovative 
Artists. 
</P>
<P>
 * Lisa Berlin was named vice president of promotions at Hamilton Projects. 
</P>
<P>
 * Peggy Powell was named vice president of creative services for Claster 
Television. 
</P>
<P>
 * Vicki D. Greenleaf was named a senior vice president of Manning, Selvage & 
Lee to run the public relations company's new entertainment group in Los 
Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
 * New Line Cinema Distribution named Larry Levy, Sue Cohen and Clayton Fellner 
to its regional sales offices. 
</P>
