<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 One Oklahoma hunter was missing Monday and about a dozen others were stranded 
in remote sections of southwestern Colorado after heavy snowstorms causing 
drifts of up to five feet blanketed the area, sheriffs' offices said. 
</P>
<P>
 "We are still searching for one hunter," said Linda Stock, spokeswoman for the 
La Plata sheriff's office in Durango. 
</P>
<P>
 Bob Chance, 45, of Ponca City, Okla., separated from three other hunters in 
his party Saturday morning and has not been seen since, she said. However, he 
was dressed warmly and had some provisions. 
</P>
