 Sheriff Russell Hebert of neighboring Archuleta County said 10 stranded 
hunters were found Sunday night and an 11th, who was lost in the adjacent 
county of Hinsdale, was found Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 The slow-moving winter-like storm over the Rockies dumped more than a foot of 
snow in parts of Colorado and Wyoming on Monday, adding to weekend 
accumulations. A winter storm warning was posted for the Big Horn Mountains. 
</P>
<P>
 The hunting season got under way Saturday. On that day a hunter from Minnesota 
accidentally shot his 33-year-old son just over the northern border with 
Wyoming, investigators said. Conditions were very foggy, they said, and the 
victim's bright orange safety vest was found near the body. 
