<P>
 American warships and Marines will arrive Thursday off Red Beach on the 
southern Philippine island of Leyte to mark the 50th anniversary of the 
landings that began the liberation of the island nation, then a U.S. territory, 
from Japanese forces in World War II. 
</P>
<P>
