<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: DIGITAL THEATER SIGNS CONTRACT WITH CARMIKE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Digital Theater Systems, a Westlake Village-based supplier of digital sound 
systems for movie theaters, will provide theater-chain giant Carmike Cinemas 
with 300 DTS sound units under a far-reaching agreement announced by the two 
companies.Terms of the deal were not disclosed. 
</P>
<P>
 Carmike will buy 300 of the digital sound systems, to be installed 
immediately. It has also committed to purchase DTS units for all new screens it 
builds over the next five years, starting with a minimum of 150 screens in 
1995. Carmike will also continue to buy DTS units to install in its existing 
multiplexes, with the goal of placing the sound systems on all 1,900 screens in 
the chain. 
</P>
