REGIONAL EARNINGS: CALNETICS' 1ST-QUARTER PROFIT 56% HIGHER THAN LAST YEAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Calnetics Corp., a Chatsworth maker of plastic components, posted a profit of 
$169,000 for the first fiscal quarter that ended Sept. 30, up 56% from $108,000 
the same period the previous year. The profit was on record sales of $6.65 
million, up 69% from $3.94 million the previous year. 
</P>
<P>
 The company attributed the gain to its acquisition in April of Agricultural 
Products Inc. and improved sales at its other subsidiaries. 
</P>
