<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: ON ASSIGNMENT HAS IMPROVED EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 On Assignment Inc., a Calabasas provider of temporary laboratory workers and 
other personnel, reported strong earnings and revenue gains for its third 
quarter and the nine months ended Sept. 30. 
</P>
<P>
 On Assignment reported a profit of $886,000 for the September quarter, a 52% 
increase from its $582,000 in net income a year before. Its revenue rose 36%, 
to $12.7 million from $9.33 million. 
</P>
<P>
 For the nine months, the company's earnings grew 38% to $2.36 million, while 
its revenue was up 27%, to $35.4 million. A year earlier, it had a $1.71 
million profit on $27.8 million in revenue. On Assignment said the improved 
results reflected increased numbers of employees on assignment and decreased 
workers' compensation insurance expenses. 
</P>
