REGIONAL EARNINGS: SUMMIT CARE PROFITS JUMP BY 30% TO $1.62 MILLION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Summit Care Corp., a Burbank operator of nursing care and other health care 
properties, reported a sharp increase in its fiscal first quarter earnings due 
to across-the-board improved results from its nursing centers. 
</P>
<P>
 In the three months ended Sept. 30, Summit Care had net income of $1.62 
million, up 30% from the $1.24 million profit of a year earlier.Its revenue 
rose 23%, to $27.2 million from $22.1 million. 
</P>
<P>
 The company also said that it completed the purchase of the operations and 
leasehold interests in six nursing care centers, and the operations and real 
estate of a seventh nursing care center, for about $11.5 million in cash and a 
$3-million note. The centers, all in Texas, have combined annual revenues of 
$14 million. 
