<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: STANTON; CITY REVISES POWERS OF MANAGER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TOM RAGAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Department heads in the city will now report to City Manager Greg Hulsizer. 
They will also be hired by Hulsizer, who has been working for the city for a 
little over a year. 
</P>
<P>
 The City Council voted last week to amend the city code, which requires that 
the council hire all department heads, such as the directors for public works 
and community services. 
</P>
<P>
 The city decided to revise the city manager's powers at a workshop in 
December, 1993. Hulsizer said it is standard procedure in most cities for 
department heads to be hired by the city manager. 
</P>
<P>
 A contract establishing levels of compensation, severance pay and other 
benefits also will be drawn up between the city manager and the department 
heads under the new ordinance. 
</P>
<P>
 But Hulsizer is not invincible, as Councilman Harry Dotson pointed out just 
before voting: The city manager is under contract by the City Council and must 
report to the council. TOM RAGAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
