<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: TUSTIN; RECREATION PROGRAM FOR SCHOOLS CONSIDERED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Tustin Unified School District is forming an advisory panel to consider 
creation of a recreation department for the school district. 
</P>
<P>
 The department, modeled after a similar program at the Saddleback Unified 
School District, would provide recreational services to all schools in the 
district, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition, the department could also provide youth, sports, and recreational 
services to the city of Tustin and unincorporated areas. 
</P>
<P>
 Those interested in serving on the panel may submit their name, address and 
telephone number to Supt. David Andrews, 300 S. C St., Tustin. The deadline is 
4:30 p.m. Wednesday. For more information, call (714) 730-7305. BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</TEXT>
