when he fell nine feet and landed on his head while working on a 45-foot 
fishing yacht at Lido Shipyard, 1010 Shipyard Way, said Rick McAnally, a senior 
deputy coroner. Najera was dead on arrival at Hoag Memorial Hospital 
Presbyterian in Newport Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 The coroner's office and police are still investigating the incident, but do 
not suspect foul play. 
