<HEADLINE>
<P>
CENTRAL LIBRARY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Just when my love affair with Los Angeles had begun to wane, I made the effort 
to visit the Central Library and celebrate its first anniversary since its 
reconstruction and addition.What a joy to behold humanity, in all of its 
guises, collecting around a central and very important part of our city. 
</P>
<P>
 The canopy in the Bradley Wing bursts forth with color and design, sending an 
energy to all who pass through. The magnificent rotunda with its fabulous mural 
is truly dazzling. The juxtaposition of the old and new is sublime. 
</P>
<P>
 You have renewed my love for you, Los Angeles, by providing me with the 
perfect jewel, the Central Library. Thank you.  
</P>
<P>
 JULIANN KERN 
</P>
<P>
 Tarzana 
</P>
