<P>
EMIR OF QATAR'S RELATIVE ROBBED OF HER JEWELS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Highway robbers posing as police stopped a sister-in-law of the Emir of Qatar 
on her way to a Paris airport over the weekend and made off with her jewels, 
French media reported Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 They said her driver obeyed signals to stop from the phony plainclothes police 
officers in a car with flashing blue lights. 
</P>
<P>
 The robbers seized jewels, cash and suitcases and fled with the car keys, 
stranding the vehicle just north of Paris. 
</P>
