<HEADLINE>
<P>
CLASS ACTION SUIT TARGETS ABBEY ACQUISITION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Abbey Healthcare Group Inc. in Costa Mesa said Monday that a federal class 
action complaint had against the corporation, Chairman Timothy M. Aitken, 
former Abbey executive Victor M.G. Chaltiel, 10 other individuals and several 
investment companies, including Prudential Ventures Partners II, Sequoia 
Capital IV and the Sequoia Capital Growth Fund. 
</P>
<P>
 The complaint, filed in U.S. District Court in the Central District of 
California by Barbara Nowack, a registered shareholder of 100 shares, alleges 
violations of the securities laws during the course of Abbey's acquisition of 
Total Pharmaceutical Care Inc. beginning in November, 1993, and seeks 
compensatory damages including interest, costs and other relief. 
</P>
<P>
 Abbey and Chaltiel, who operated Total Pharmaceutical before the merger, have 
been suing each other for the last several months ago in connection with that 
transaction. 
</P>
