<P>
ATHLETES OF THE WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Adalberto Sanchez 
</P>
<P>
 Capistrano Valley, Senior 
</P>
<P>
 Cross-country 
</P>
<P>
 After running his usual blistering first mile, Sanchez had no competition at 
the Orange County Championships Saturday at Irvine Regional Park. "I heard 
someone say he was in the 4:30s in the first mile, which is pretty scary for 
the other guys," Capistrano Valley Coach Gary Gross said."A lot of people think 
he's being a maniac, but he's comfortable going out that fast." Sanchez 
finished the 3.1-mile course in 15:13 and won the race by 15 seconds. Sanchez, 
who won the Southern Section Division I-AA title last year, also ran 15:11 for 
three miles to help the Cougars to a dual-meet victory over San Clemente. 
Football 
</P>
